        "locked": false,
        "title": "Generate secretref reference docs from secret target registry metadata",
        "body": "## Problem\n\n`src/secrets/target-registry.test.ts` currently catches drift between code and docs after the fact, but the secretref reference docs are still manually synced:\n\n- `docs/reference/secretref-user-supplied-credentials-matrix.json`\n- `docs/reference/secretref-credential-surface.md`\n\nThis creates recurring branch churn where code changes are correct, but docs/reference artifacts fall out of sync and only fail later in CI.\n\n## Why It Matters\n\n- Contributors get avoidable CI failures on unrelated branches.\n- Secretref support changes require editing multiple sources of truth.\n- Docs and tests are harder to trust when drift is common.\n\n## Suggested Direction\n\nUse the registry metadata as the single source of truth and generate the reference artifacts from code.\n\nPossible approach:\n\n- add a generation script for the matrix JSON and surface doc blocks\n- check generated outputs into the repo if desired\n- keep the existing parity tests, but point them at generated outputs\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- Secretref reference docs are derived from one canonical source.\n- Updating secret target registry metadata does not require hand-editing multiple docs files.\n- CI drift failures become much less common and easier to fix.\n",
